description.narrative:
The project global objective is to contribute to ensuring a safe and responsible management of sexuality and reducing gender-based violence in schools in Burkina Faso. The project has&nbsp;03 spefic objectives:
1. To promote responsible ans safe sexual behavior in schools.
2. Advocate for the harmonization of interventions and effective integration of sex education into the training curricula.
3. Reduce gender based violence in schools in particular sexual violence.&nbsp;
The project is an extension of previous period. Durong 2012-2014, advocacy and sensitization actions were conducted. The project has produced good results, but the&nbsp;problem analysis of the intervention , the rate of unwanted&nbsp;pregancy at schools level remains. During the school years 2012 to 2015, in total 344 cases were registered in&nbsp;central Plateau region schools. It is clear that students are becoming more sexually active with an unprecedented precocity.
So over the next five years, several tools of awareness and training will be used during training sessions for students and adults. Social media will also use&nbsp;to adopt responsible sexual behavior among young people.&nbsp;Oral arguments will be conducted at the location of the different actors for each plays its role in good sexual education for students.To harmonize interventions and effective integration of Sexual and Reproduction Health in the secondary school, the CRIGED will assist decision makers in the education system in the problem analysis, the proposal and the adoption of adequate solutions, by advocacy.
Through these actions, the following results will be achieved:-Responsible sexual behavior are promoted in schools through the use of social media in particular media.-Sexual health and reproduction is effectively integrated into training curricula through harmonized interventions-Victims of violence based on gender in schools in particular sexual violence are 
The project will be implemented by the Centre de&nbsp;Recherche et d'intervention en Genre (CRIGED),&nbsp;&nbsp;mainly in the region of the central plateau but the results will benefit the youth from secondary schools from all regions of Burkina Faso.
The mains thematic focus are chid&nbsp;right and gender based&nbsp;violence.&nbsp;
